**Trie approach**: Build a trie of all words. Walk from root: as long as the current node has exactly one child AND is not the end of any word, append that child's character.

**Vertical scan (simpler, equivalent)**: Pick the first word; for each column index `i`, ensure every other word has the same char at `i`. Stop on first mismatch or when any word ends.

```javascript
function longestCommonPrefix(words) {
  if (words.length === 0) return "";
  const first = words[0];
  for (let i = 0; i < first.length; i++) {
    const c = first[i];
    for (let j = 1; j < words.length; j++) {
      if (i >= words[j].length || words[j][i] !== c) {
        return first.slice(0, i);
      }
    }
